 Kogi State Governor, Yahaya Bello  The plant will provide electricity to un-served and underserved communities across the state and the country by increasing electricity access to remote areas. Speaking at the commissioning ceremony in Ukake, Managing Director of the Rural Electrification Agency (REA), Damilola Ogunbiyi, said President Muhammed Buhari was committed to reducing the sufferings of Nigerians through the provision of critical infrastructure. She said the construction of the multi-million Naira Solar power in Ukake was one of such efforts of the Buhari administration aimed at meeting the needs of rural dwellers in the country. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .